Relic Terminology Standard — Industry‑Aligned Artifact Definition

Description
In VaultForge‑Live, the term Relic is intentionally used as the system’s sovereign identifier for what the broader industry calls an artifact. This alignment ensures that all relics remain fully compatible with industry, legal, and evidentiary standards without adopting external terminology that could dilute authorship or introduce interpretive ambiguity.

